    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped out or not assessed per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 for a Class II device at MRL 2. The CFD model demonstrates reasonable predictive performance for hemolysis index across the validated operating range. Turbulence model and hemolysis model form sensitivity analyses confirm minimal impact on worst-case operating condition identification. The requirement that the model exhibit 'reasonable performance' with 'minimal impact' from model form uncertainty is satisfied based on the team's engineering judgment and internal assessment guidelines, consistent with accepted practice for blood pump CFD submissions at this risk level. Overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory use.",
